# ArgoCD Notifications: allows to send Dynatrace Events
[ArgoCD Notifications](https://argocd-notifications.readthedocs.io) are a way to send notifications for on-create, on-delete, on-deployed, on-health-degraded, on-sync-failed, on-sync-running, on-sync-status-unknown, on-sync-succeeded triggers to external tools

To send information to Dynatrace we can use the [Webhook Notification Services](https://argocd-notifications.readthedocs.io/en/stable/services/webhook/)

## Webhook Notifications Configuration for Dynatrace

The following is a snippet of the argocd-notifications-cm ConfigMap that uses the Webhook Integration to send a message to the Dynatrace Events API v2 on e.g: app-sync-succeeded!

```
apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: argocd-notifications-cm
  namespace: argocd
data:
  service.webhook.dynatrace: |
    url: $dynatrace-url
    headers:
    - name: Authorization
      value: Api-Token $dynatrace-token
    - name: Content-Type
      value: application/json
  template.app-sync-succeeded: |
    webhook:
      dynatrace:
        method: POST
        path: /api/v2/events/ingest
        body: |
          {
            "eventType" : "CUSTOM_INFO",
            "title": "ArgoCD: app-sync-succeeded: {{.app.metadata.name}}",
            "properties": {
              "action" : "app-sync-succeeded",
              "repo_url": "{{.app.spec.source.repoURL}}",
              "revisions" : "{{.app.status.operationState.operation.sync.revision}}",
              "commit_url" : "{{.app.spec.source.repoURL}}/-/commit/{{.app.status.operationState.operation.sync.revision}}",
              "target_url" : "{{.context.argocdUrl}}/applications/{{.app.metadata.name}}",
              "app_name": "{{.app.metadata.name}}",
              "source" : "ArgoCD",
              "sync_status" : "{{.app.status.sync.status}}",
              "synced_at" : "{{.app.status.operationState.finishedAt}}"
            }
          }

    ...

  trigger.on-sync-succeeded: |
    - description: Application syncing has succeeded
      send:
      - app-sync-succeeded
      when: app.status.operationState != nil and app.status.operationState.phase in ['Succeeded']       
```
